as a courtesy.

16
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:19,960
Just a moment.

17
00:02:20,719 --> 00:02:21,560
Damn.

18
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:28,199
I have to go to Ander's
to get the rest of my stuff.

19
00:02:28,479 --> 00:02:30,080
After that, I don't know...

20
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:32,840
Maybe I'll perform hara-kiri
over my grades.

21
00:02:32,919 --> 00:02:34,360
Were they really that bad?

22
00:02:36,319 --> 00:02:38,039
On a scale of disasters...

23
00:02:38,599 --> 00:02:39,960
the Notre-Dame fire,

24
00:02:40,319 --> 00:02:41,680
Spain at Eurovision,

25
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,800
-Madonna at Eurovision...
-Damn.

26
00:02:43,879 --> 00:02:44,719
...my grades.

27
00:02:48,479 --> 00:02:51,560
I have to laugh
because if I really think about it...

28
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:55,240
In the end, I'm not graduating,
I've lost Ander...

29
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:56,879
and I'm homeless.

30
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,319
What?

31
00:03:06,919 --> 00:03:08,919
Why don't you come to New York with me?

32
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:12,439
-What?
-Come on.

33
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:14,479
You've always wanted to travel

34
00:03:14,719 --> 00:03:17,280
and live somewhere
where you could blend in.

35
00:03:17,599 --> 00:03:20,960
New York meets that criteria
better than any place I can think of.

36
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:24,319
You'll get a job, learn English...

37
00:03:24,759 --> 00:03:26,479
What the hell would I do there?

38
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:28,960
Where would I stay?

39
00:03:30,599 --> 00:03:31,879
It's crazy, Nadia.

40
00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:35,159
