All you care about is money and power.

67
00:05:15,879 --> 00:05:18,560
-Don't talk to me like that.
-Or what? You'll expel us?

68
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:24,120
Samu... it's not worth it.

69
00:05:25,199 --> 00:05:26,439
What are you doing?

70
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,639
What's he doing? Stop!

71
00:05:30,199 --> 00:05:31,639
-What are you doing?
-Relax.

72
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,199
That's enough violence, OK?

73
00:05:33,279 --> 00:05:34,920
-Are you defending him?
-Yes!

74
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,319
He said he didn't accuse you two
of anything.

75
00:05:37,759 --> 00:05:38,959
And you believe him?

76
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:49,079
You're doing this so you won't feel bad
about accepting the grant.

77
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:52,800
You'll accept it no matter what,
even if it means taking his side.

78
00:05:59,759 --> 00:06:00,800
Son of a bitch.

79
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:03,720
Lu, forget about him.

80
00:06:04,639 --> 00:06:06,399
Nadia, don't play innocent.

81
00:06:06,759 --> 00:06:09,759
You want to smash this bottle
over his head as much as I do.

82
00:06:09,879 --> 00:06:10,879
Admit it.

83
00:06:20,319 --> 00:06:23,040
This wouldn't have happened
if they'd just let me leave.

84
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:26,920
That doesn't matter now. 
We need to think of a way to fix this.

85
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:27,839
We could--

86
00:06:28,839 --> 00:06:30,519
It's too late. It's over.

87
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:35,040
-You can't end things this way.
-Carla almost drowned last night.

88
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:37,079
She almost died because of him.

89
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:41,319
Because of me! It was my fault, OK?

90
00:06:41,839 --> 00:06:43,079
What are you saying?

91
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:46,319
I sold Carla the Molly
'cause Valerio refused.

92
00:06:46,399 --> 00:06:49,399
He was going to stop dealing
after your little lecture.

93
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:54,199
What? You didn't know? Well, now you do.

94
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:57,040
But you had to go and make a scene.

95
00:06:57,240 --> 00:07:00,720
I guess you couldn't bear the idea
of doing something right for once.

96
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:04,639
-Why don't you go home, Rebeka?
-Fucking Bodyguard Barbie.

97
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:07,759
Better yet, just go straight to jail.

98
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:11,920
-You'll end up there with your mom anyway.
-We have something in common.

99
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,279
Because you also get along great
with criminals.

100
00:07:14,759 --> 00:07:18,000
As long as they pay for your outfits,
expensive meals, and tuition...

101
00:07:18,079 --> 00:07:20,399
But I get it, OK? I really do.

102
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:24,000
Hold on to him tight.
You know what you'll have once he's gone?

103
00:07:24,839 --> 00:07:26,399
Nothing and no one, hon.

104
00:07:32,399 --> 00:07:34,120
Damn private number!

105
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:48,480
You don't look too bad...
at least not at first glance.

106
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,600
-I can't remember a thing.
-That's normal.

107
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:55,639
No, it's not. 

108
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,519
I lost control.

109
00:07:57,759 --> 00:08:01,560
-And I helped you lose it. I'm sorry.
-No, you warned me.

110
00:08:02,319 --> 00:08:06,040
I'm the one who's sorry. 
I just heard you were expelled.

111
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:08,439
He got what was coming to him.

112
00:08:08,519 --> 00:08:11,680
Don't blame him for yesterday.
He wouldn't sell to me.

113
00:08:11,759 --> 00:08:15,759
Well, it's the first bit of common sense
he's shown in ages,

114
00:08:15,839 --> 00:08:18,839
-but it's still too late.
-Well, later.

115
00:08:21,439 --> 00:08:24,079
I've been trying to change
for a long time.

116
00:08:24,519 --> 00:08:25,519
Trying...

117
00:08:26,399 --> 00:08:27,879
but you never change.

118
00:08:28,439 --> 00:08:31,399
-You'll never grow up.
-I had nothing to do with what happened.

119
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:33,360
You're like a fucking baby...

120
00:08:33,759 --> 00:08:36,240
sticking his fingers
in electrical sockets.

121
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:40,399
For 17 years, I've tried to stop you
from electrocuting yourself...

122
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,440
but it's never enough.

123
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,600
I can't take it anymore.

124
00:08:47,639 --> 00:08:48,960
Have a good life.

125
00:08:55,759 --> 00:08:58,519
He always wins.
I'm fucking sick of this.

126
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:02,039
-We should've moved on a long time ago.
-We didn't do anything to him!

127
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:04,879
Not today,
but look at everything we've done

128
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:07,039
to make his life a living hell.

129
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:11,080
Not a single day has gone by
that we haven't hated him,

130
00:09:11,159 --> 00:09:12,480
and we made sure he knew it.

131
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:15,759
He didn't win... We lost.

132
00:09:20,759 --> 00:09:21,879
Guzmán.

133
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,000
-How are you?
-Fine.

134
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,360
I know you.

135
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:32,759
What they did to you is a disgrace.

136
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,279
We deserved it.

137
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:38,039
What? It can't end like this.

138
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:41,559
-I swear--
-Stay out of wars that don't affect you.

139
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:46,399
They affect me...
if they hurt someone I love.

140
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:48,759
You can't risk your scholarship. 
It's your future.

141
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,600
What about yours? Doesn't it matter?

142
00:09:53,399 --> 00:09:54,720
I'm 17 years old.

143
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:58,279
I can afford
to put the future on hold for a year.

144
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,320
Hey...

145
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,720
After graduation, we'll throw a party.

146
00:10:05,799 --> 00:10:08,759
We'll have a blast.
Nothing will fuck it up.

147
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:10,960
I promise.

148
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:14,039
Give me a light, honey.

149
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:21,039
You never smoke on the job.

150
00:10:30,279 --> 00:10:31,960
Those kids will be the end of me.

151
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:36,360
The school year's almost over,
but they'll be the end of me.

152
00:10:38,279 --> 00:10:41,039
What you did is unfair, you know.

153
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:44,519
-Please, not you too.
-What do you want me to say?

154
00:10:45,159 --> 00:10:49,879
It's not a question of being fair or not.
It's much more complicated.

155
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:55,159
-You'd need to be in my shoes to get it.
-But Guzmán and Samu don't deserve this.

156
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,360
Focus on the important stuff.

157
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,080
Your exams, for example.

158
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:03,279
I'm not taking any makeup exams.

159
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:07,440
Don't start with that nonsense
about favoritism again.

160
00:11:07,519 --> 00:11:10,960
Allowing you to retake exams due to chemo
isn't favoritism.

161
00:11:12,159 --> 00:11:15,320
I'm not wasting my last few days of life
in front of a book.

162
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:18,240
What do you mean, "last days"?

163
00:11:21,159 --> 00:11:22,799
There's no hope for me...

164
00:11:23,559 --> 00:11:25,159
at least not down the road.

165
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:27,879
-And...
-Where'd you get that idea, Ander?

166
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:32,080
Who told you that? No one told me that.

167
00:11:32,919 --> 00:11:35,840
This is all I have. The here and now.

168
00:11:37,519 --> 00:11:38,399
But, honey...

169
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:41,039
OK, and maybe tomorrow.

170
00:11:42,399 --> 00:11:45,000
But I won't waste my time studying.
What for?

171
00:11:46,519 --> 00:11:49,320
I won't allow
this resigned, defeated attitude.

172
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,279
Mom...

173
00:11:50,879 --> 00:11:53,879
You don't want to study?
What do you want to do, then?

174
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:58,320
I don't know.

175
00:11:59,559 --> 00:12:01,559
Spend some time with myself.

176
00:12:04,799 --> 00:12:06,200
Start preparing myself.

177
00:12:12,559 --> 00:12:14,600
You'd need to be in my shoes to get it.

178
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:38,080
HI, YERAY. WHEN CAN WE MEET?
YERAY, PLEASE ANSWER ME.

179
00:12:38,159 --> 00:12:40,039
ARE YOU OK? CAN I CALL YOU?

180
00:13:10,159 --> 00:13:12,200
FROM: MOM
SUBJECT: GOOD NEWS!!!

181
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:20,720
The lawyer wants to meet
with my mom and brother in Morocco.

182
00:13:20,799 --> 00:13:23,600
-He says he has good news.
-That's fucking awesome.

183
00:13:24,879 --> 00:13:28,039
Maybe this nightmare will be over,
and Nano can come home.

184
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:31,480
It's not over as long as Polo's free.

185
00:13:32,159 --> 00:13:35,759
