to talk to me.

251
00:17:59,039 --> 00:18:01,599
That's fine, but I'm asking you...

252
00:18:02,119 --> 00:18:03,599
please talk to your moms.

253
00:18:03,680 --> 00:18:07,880
They could get them to readmit Valerio
and forgive him because...

254
00:18:08,079 --> 00:18:12,359
there's no sense in punishing him
when he'd already learned his lesson.

255
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:15,680
Please, whatever you decide, call me.

256
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,279
Please, OK?

257
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,000
What are you wearing tomorrow?

258
00:18:23,319 --> 00:18:24,359
I'm not going, Mom.

259
00:18:26,039 --> 00:18:28,640
The students who won't be graduating...

260
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:31,319
got what they deserved.

261
00:18:31,519 --> 00:18:32,839
And Guzmán and Samuel?

262
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:35,319
They just broke up the fight.

263
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:39,920
Those bullies have been making
your life hell all year.

264
00:18:40,359 --> 00:18:42,720
If you're not man enough to face them...

265
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:46,359
you can't expect me to stand by
and watch my son get beaten up.

266
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:50,559
How about the striped shirt...

267
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,279
with the blue pants?

268
00:18:55,559 --> 00:18:57,079
You'll look so handsome.

269
00:19:19,279 --> 00:19:20,519
What're you doing here?

270
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:25,559
What's up with you?

271
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:31,960
How'd you get in?
I don't have a doorman you can manipulate.

272
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:40,119
From when you asked me
to decorate the place and make it my own.

273
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:41,039
Yeah...

274
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:44,319
Those were good times.

275
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:48,920
Please, take a seat. Get comfy.

276
00:19:52,279 --> 00:19:53,839
Why are you here, Carla?

277
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,680
I came to apologize.

278
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:57,119
For real.

279
00:19:57,799 --> 00:19:59,359
You're a really great guy.

280
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:04,519
"Yeray, you're a great guy.
You're really worth it,

281
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:06,920
any girl would kill to be with you..."

282
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,440
Except the one who says it, of course.
Been there.

283
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:11,000
I really mean it.

284
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:16,799
Carla, the last thing I need now
is your pity, really.

285
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:19,440
-Please leave.
-All right...

286
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:24,160
Let's stop playing the victim...
because you don't like me either.

287
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,000
-Excuse me?
-You heard me.

288
00:20:29,359 --> 00:20:32,240
I don't like you,
and you don't like me either.

289
00:20:32,319 --> 00:20:34,079
What about the last few months?

290
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:36,440
-What do you call--
-You love what I represent.

291
00:20:36,519 --> 00:20:38,720
How well I fit in
with the image you created

292
00:20:38,799 --> 00:20:42,200
to get likes from people
who hurt the old Yeray.

293
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:46,359
Your body, your clothes, your attitude...

294
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:50,400
You even created your own social network
to get them to worship you.

295
00:20:51,319 --> 00:20:53,559
All I am to you is another accessory.

296
00:20:54,319 --> 00:20:57,359
And I'm a walking checkbook
meant to save your wineries.

297
00:20:57,440 --> 00:20:58,720
That's what I meant!

298
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,920
We don't like each other
the way we pretend to.

299
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:08,599
Even so, I was lucky enough
to get to know the real Yeray,

300
00:21:08,759 --> 00:21:10,240
the one behind the selfies.

301
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:13,200
And I can tell you... he's a great guy.

302
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:16,119
Much better than the one you made up.

303
00:21:17,839 --> 00:21:20,920
And I bet any girl
would kill to be with you.

304
00:21:21,279 --> 00:21:22,400
Any girl but me.

305
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:28,799
So...

306
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:31,119
fuck the likes...

307
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:33,440
and fuck the wineries.

308
00:21:34,079 --> 00:21:38,759
We've already wasted enough time
doing what others want us to do, right?

309
00:21:43,559 --> 00:21:45,559
You have nothing to prove to anyone.

310
00:21:48,119 --> 00:21:49,920
Now... can I give you a hug?

311
00:21:50,759 --> 00:21:53,839
As a friend, not trying to manipulate you.

312
00:22:07,880 --> 00:22:10,400
-Are you nervous, honey?
-A little, Dad.

313
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:11,519
It'll be fine.

314
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:12,880
There's Omar!

315
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:20,160
-How are you, Mom?
-I'm fine.

316
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:21,400
You look great.

317
00:22:22,160 --> 00:22:23,039
You too.

318
00:22:23,279 --> 00:22:24,200
How are you?

319
00:22:24,559 --> 00:22:25,680
A bit nervous.

320
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:27,559
About what? Come on.

321
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:28,480
Hey.

322
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:30,079
-Hello.
-Hi, Lu.

323
00:22:31,319 --> 00:22:32,279
I like it.

324
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:34,519
-Hey, Lu.
-What's up?

325
00:22:36,079 --> 00:22:37,599
Didn't your parents come?

326
00:22:40,079 --> 00:22:44,160
It seems your family knows how
to put problems aside for a while...

327
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:46,200
to focus on what matters.

328
00:22:48,359 --> 00:22:49,319
I envy you.

329
00:22:50,119 --> 00:22:53,079
In a good way.... and in a bad way too.

330
00:22:53,519 --> 00:22:54,720
You look like a pistachio.

331
00:22:56,839 --> 00:22:58,680
You can't make an exception?

332
00:22:58,759 --> 00:23:00,720
After all I've done
for this fucking school!

333
00:23:00,799 --> 00:23:03,640
-Please!
-I'll take you to court.

334
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:05,279
Come in, please.

335
00:23:05,359 --> 00:23:09,200
Ventura, do what you think is best,
but the expulsion was justified.

336
00:23:09,279 --> 00:23:10,319
Justified?

337
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,960
On the last day of the year? Oh, please.

338
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:15,519
My son's entire year,
thrown away on the last day!

339
00:23:15,599 --> 00:23:18,839
-Laura, Ventura, I--
-Lucrecia, honey, stay out of this.

340
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:22,440
Actually, I wish you'd done more
to help Guzmán.

341
00:23:23,079 --> 00:23:26,519
-Me?
-Yes. Your father's very influential.

342
00:23:26,599 --> 00:23:29,519
-If we all did our part--
-Okay, that's enough.

343
00:23:30,039 --> 00:23:31,200
I'm very sorry.

344
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:45,039
Polo!

345
00:23:45,839 --> 00:23:48,000
How are you? So?

346
00:23:48,799 --> 00:23:50,200
Why are you ignoring me?

347
00:23:54,359 --> 00:23:56,400
They still haven't signed the papers.

348
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:58,200
-We'll talk to your--
-Cayetana.

349
00:23:58,279 --> 00:24:00,640
Why are you so set on Valerio graduating?

350
00:24:03,839 --> 00:24:07,160
-So he can come with us and--
-And save our relationship.

351
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:11,839
Because... without him...

352
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:13,799
we just don't work.

353
00:24:15,359 --> 00:24:16,880
Polo, don't start.

354
00:24:18,359 --> 00:24:19,440
Don't start.

355
00:24:21,319 --> 00:24:23,599
I get it. You're under a lot of pressure.

356
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:26,480
-You don't know what you're saying.
-No.

357
00:24:26,559 --> 00:24:29,079
For the first time in a long time, I know.

358
00:24:33,119 --> 00:24:34,000
I'm sorry.

359
00:24:41,039 --> 00:24:43,880
What about... London? Our plans?

360
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:46,359
See? That's all you're worried about.

361
00:24:46,759 --> 00:24:48,160
London, our plans...

362
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:53,880
You're not in love with me...
but with the life I would've provided.

363
00:24:56,839 --> 00:24:58,799
Why are you using the past tense?

364
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:04,680
I'm sorry.

365
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:09,559
I have to go, OK?

366
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:27,839
Hey...

367
00:25:28,359 --> 00:25:29,200
What happened?

368
00:25:30,559 --> 00:25:31,400
Nothing.

369
00:25:51,599 --> 00:25:55,440
Hold on... one sec. I won't be long.

370
00:25:58,680 --> 00:25:59,559
Teodoro.

371
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:05,839
Can we meet at your place later
to close the deal?

372
00:26:09,839 --> 00:26:10,680
Of course.

373
00:26:11,359 --> 00:26:13,000
I'm glad you reconsidered.

374
00:26:14,559 --> 00:26:16,960
The ceremony will start in five minutes.

375
00:26:17,519 --> 00:26:18,359
There he is.

376
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:47,000
Thank you.

377
00:26:47,319 --> 00:26:48,640
Let's continue.

378
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:51,319
Shit...

379
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:53,480
Let me do it.

380
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:57,039
The students I'm about to introduce...

381
00:26:57,119 --> 00:26:58,240
What should we do?

382
00:26:59,319 --> 00:27:00,519
I really don't know.

383
00:27:01,319 --> 00:27:04,079
All I know is I want that scholarship.

384
00:27:04,160 --> 00:27:06,559
So do I. But we're selling out.

385
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:10,039
So, you don't want it?

386
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:12,559
At what price?

387
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:17,000
Can the winners of the first edition
of the scholarship please come up?

388
00:27:17,079 --> 00:27:18,400
A big round of applause

389
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:21,680
for Nadia Shanaa
and Lucrecia Montesinos Hendrich.

390
00:27:38,599 --> 00:27:43,000
Bill McKinley will present the award
on behalf of Columbia University.

391
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:14,880
Good afternoon.

392
00:28:16,279 --> 00:28:20,440
I want to thank our parents and friends
who have come to share

393
00:28:20,519 --> 00:28:22,039
in this special moment...

394
00:28:22,119 --> 00:28:25,480
for us and... for our fellow students.

395
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:30,039
I would like--

396
00:28:33,680 --> 00:28:34,559
I can't.

397
00:28:42,039 --> 00:28:43,839
Can you speak for me, Nadia?

398
00:28:44,039 --> 00:28:45,799
No, you've already started.

399
00:28:49,759 --> 00:28:50,640
Well...

400
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:53,799
-I was saying that--
-No, wait.

401
00:28:56,359 --> 00:28:58,599
I would just like to say that...

402
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:01,799
I would like to--

403
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:03,400
We would like to...

404
00:29:03,839 --> 00:29:05,559
I think I speak for us both.

405
00:29:07,119 --> 00:29:08,599
We dedicate this award...

406
00:29:09,559 --> 00:29:11,039
to our classmates.

407
00:29:11,119 --> 00:29:13,920
Especially everyone in the back...

408
00:29:15,799 --> 00:29:19,720
who, for various reasons,
cannot join us... up here...

409
00:29:20,599 --> 00:29:22,279
in this graduation ceremony.

410
00:29:35,319 --> 00:29:37,799
Not being able to have them
here with us...

411
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:41,400
makes this moment...

412
00:29:42,039 --> 00:29:44,480
less happy than we would have liked.

413
00:29:44,960 --> 00:29:45,799
That's right.

414
00:29:46,079 --> 00:29:48,359
We should be jumping for joy.

415
00:29:52,799 --> 00:29:53,680
But we're not.

416
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:59,279
Because we deserve... this award.

417
00:30:00,680 --> 00:30:02,559
We deserve this moment, Nadia.

418
00:30:05,599 --> 00:30:06,759
My friends are there...

419
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:10,880
due to a series of injustices.

420
00:30:13,039 --> 00:30:14,720
Including the most serious one.

421
00:30:16,079 --> 00:30:20,519
The one that deprived us... of Marina.

422
00:30:22,039 --> 00:30:25,279
These are injustices...
that we both denounce.

423
00:30:25,519 --> 00:30:26,400
That's right.

424
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:29,680
And one person is responsible
for all those injustices.

425
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:31,480
Polo...

426
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:34,880
How are you? Happy?

427
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:36,839
I cannot believe this.

428
00:30:38,519 --> 00:30:39,880
Look, this award

429
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:41,799
that she and I are receiving...

430
00:30:42,880 --> 00:30:46,000
was created by your moms
to clean up your image, basically.

431
00:30:46,079 --> 00:30:49,519
And we're accepting it because,
I repeat, we deserve it.

432
00:30:49,759 --> 00:30:52,759
What else should we do?
Because this has become--

433
00:30:52,839 --> 00:30:55,319
If you feel so conflicted, don't worry.

434
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:58,559
The scholarship's called off.

435
00:30:58,640 --> 00:30:59,680
-Begoña, please.
-No.

436
00:31:02,680 --> 00:31:07,160
We have always wanted to support
Las Encinas and every student in it.

437
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:10,799
Who went into the bathroom?

438
00:31:14,839 --> 00:31:16,799
Omar, I don't have all day.

439
00:31:16,880 --> 00:31:20,480
And if I did, I don't have the patience.
Give me a name.

440
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:25,519
Nadia.

441
00:31:27,839 --> 00:31:29,680
You're accusing your own sister?

442
00:31:44,039 --> 00:31:44,880
You know what?

443
00:31:45,440 --> 00:31:47,960
I promised someone I love very much...

444
00:31:48,880 --> 00:31:51,680
that we would celebrate this day together.

445
00:31:52,519 --> 00:31:54,119
And that we would have lots of fun,

446
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:56,759
and that nothing and nobody
would fuck it up.

447
00:31:57,039 --> 00:31:59,440
Let's go celebrate at Teatro Barceló!

448
00:32:15,519 --> 00:32:16,359
Hello?

449
00:32:16,759 --> 00:32:17,599
Samuel.

450
00:32:18,279 --> 00:32:21,680
You need to come to the police station.
It's extremely urgent.

451
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:36,640
Dad, I'm going to the bathroom.

452
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:38,400
-Wait for me outside.
-OK.

453
00:32:38,799 --> 00:32:41,640
-We don't have the money.
-We'll take out a loan.

454
00:32:47,119 --> 00:32:48,000
So?

455
00:32:49,519 --> 00:32:51,640
You don't need Nadia in New York.

456
00:32:51,839 --> 00:32:53,000
What do you mean?

457
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:55,799
-I'd never go on my own.
-You'll have me.

458
00:32:57,079 --> 00:33:00,599
Wow! I thought we were just hooking up.

459
00:33:02,079 --> 00:33:02,960
Fuck...

460
00:33:03,319 --> 00:33:05,079
-What?
-I'm sorry.

461
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:09,480
Sorry I didn't react the way you wanted.

462
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:12,200
And yes, we hooked up.

463
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:14,880
And that meant a lot to me.

464
00:33:15,759 --> 00:33:18,519
When your sister asked me
if you could come...

465
00:33:18,759 --> 00:33:20,000
it left me speechless.

466
00:33:22,920 --> 00:33:27,839
I thought Nadia's idea was crazy, too.
And it was more than just hooking up.

467
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:30,960
Maybe that's why we should do it.

468
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:35,960
If a suggestion leaves you speechless,
you have to try.

469
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:48,640
It was all a setup...

470
00:33:49,960 --> 00:33:52,680
to locate your family
and arrest your brother.

471
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:53,799
I'm sorry.

472
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:56,640
I swear, I knew nothing about it.

473
00:33:57,079 --> 00:33:58,839
They tricked me too.

474
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:01,519
And they found them?

475
00:34:04,279 --> 00:34:06,240
Your brother will be repatriated.

476
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:08,960
Oh, Samuel...

477
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:13,239
Meanwhile, the killer's
in his suit and tie, about to go free.

478
00:34:13,840 --> 00:34:16,599
-I'm sorry.
-You should be. You're also to blame.

479
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:20,559
-I told you, they tricked me too.
-Who tricked you?

480
00:34:21,519 --> 00:34:24,119
I'll tell you who.
Your bosses, your colleagues...

481
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:26,480
the fucking system you work for,
belong to,

482
00:34:26,559 --> 00:34:28,480
and won't do shit about.

483
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:31,800
That's why it's your fault.

484
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:36,639
Shit.

485
00:34:38,039 --> 00:34:40,599
I printed the document you sent me.

486
00:34:41,119 --> 00:34:43,000
If you want to review it one last time...

487
00:34:49,960 --> 00:34:50,840
No.

488
00:34:51,480 --> 00:34:53,920
No, I think... you should review it.

489
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:55,639
Yes.

490
00:34:56,079 --> 00:34:59,639
There's been a change...
in section three of clause four.

491
00:35:00,320 --> 00:35:02,000
About the management of the wineries?

492
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:05,960
You've been replaced by Carla.

493
00:35:09,880 --> 00:35:13,679
She'll be the sole and exclusive manager
of the wineries and all related assets

494
00:35:13,760 --> 00:35:16,679
as soon as she turns 18,
which won't be long now.

495
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:19,760
Look...

496
00:35:19,960 --> 00:35:23,320
You'll have nothing to do with it.
Neither will I.

497
00:35:23,639 --> 00:35:24,840
I'll stay out of it.

498
00:35:25,239 --> 00:35:26,079
So...

499
00:35:26,920 --> 00:35:28,400
Carla will be the owner.

500
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:33,360
Yeray, what you're proposing...

501
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:35,599
has never been on the table.

502
00:35:36,079 --> 00:35:36,920
It is now.

503
00:35:38,519 --> 00:35:40,199
So, you decide.

504
00:35:41,039 --> 00:35:43,679
Let your daughter support you
as she sees fit...

505
00:35:44,639 --> 00:35:46,360
or your business will go under

506
00:35:46,440 --> 00:35:48,880
and you'll have no way
to support yourself.

507
00:35:51,039 --> 00:35:54,280
She's very young
and has no clue how to run a business.

508
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:59,159
-Say something, honey.
-I say...

509
00:36:00,400 --> 00:36:01,519
I'm done taking orders.

510
00:36:02,119 --> 00:36:02,960
Excuse me?

511
00:36:03,239 --> 00:36:04,079
I say...

512
00:36:04,159 --> 00:36:07,519
you aren't going to decide
what I can or can't do anymore.

513
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:09,000
It's over.

514
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:12,239
I want to do whatever I want...

515
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:14,480
be whatever I want...

516
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:17,079
and be with whoever I want.

517
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:19,960
You have no power over me.

518
00:36:22,320 --> 00:36:23,559
So, what do you say?

519
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:25,400
Shall we sign?

520
00:36:31,679 --> 00:36:33,920
You know who's to blame? Azucena.

521
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:36,360
She doesn't command respect
from her students.

522
00:36:36,440 --> 00:36:39,320
-She fears them and spoils them.
-It was a childish prank.

523
00:36:39,400 --> 00:36:41,519
Canceling the scholarship
was an overreaction.

524
00:36:41,599 --> 00:36:43,239
At least I did something.

525
00:36:43,320 --> 00:36:44,320
If it wasn't for me,

526
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:48,480
the bullies who made your son's life hell
would still be in school.

527
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:51,159
-Maybe I deserved it.
-What do you mean?

528
00:36:51,239 --> 00:36:54,400
Don't be ridiculous.
After everything that's happened...

529
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:56,119
the bullying, the tweets,

530
00:36:56,199 --> 00:36:58,000
everything they wrote, all the hurt.

531
00:36:58,079 --> 00:37:02,000
-To top it off, the person in charge--
-I killed Marina, Mom!

532
00:37:08,599 --> 00:37:11,760
-It was an accident, but I did.
-Enough of this nonsense.

533
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:13,559
-Begoña.
-I don't want to hear it.

534
00:37:13,639 --> 00:37:15,800
Marina had something
that belonged to Carla...

535
00:37:17,920 --> 00:37:19,880
and I wanted to get it
to get Carla back.

536
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:21,719
-Polo, enough.
-No!

537
00:37:23,320 --> 00:37:26,519
Fuck, Mom.
You always tell me to be a man.

538
00:37:28,239 --> 00:37:32,360
To face up to things, to be brave.
Well, that's what I'm doing.

539
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:35,000
I killed Marina...

540
00:37:38,599 --> 00:37:40,199
I can't bring her back.

541
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:47,320
I can't help Samuel and Guzmán graduate.
But don't cancel the scholarship.

542
00:37:50,599 --> 00:37:54,599
At least let someone have a happy ending
in this awful story.

543
00:37:58,239 --> 00:37:59,760
So, please call now.

544
00:38:01,800 --> 00:38:02,679
Please.

545
00:38:06,280 --> 00:38:08,760
Azucena? Yes, hi. It's Begoña.

546
00:38:08,840 --> 00:38:11,480
I'm sorry to be calling so late, but...

547
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:14,480
I want to talk... about the scholarship.

548
00:38:34,880 --> 00:38:35,800
Hi.

549
00:38:36,360 --> 00:38:38,199
-Have you seen Samuel?
-Nope.

550
00:38:45,039 --> 00:38:47,360
Should we hijack the DJ booth
to liven things up?

551
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:50,079
No music
can lift the funk hanging over all of us.

552
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:52,400
So, I lost the scholarship.

553
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:55,199
You two just had to play the heroines.

554
00:38:57,039 --> 00:38:59,639
-What now?
-Let me use one of your questions.

555
00:39:02,119 --> 00:39:03,679
Where does that leave us?

556
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:06,360
Define "that."

557
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:10,400
The fact that I'm not going.
That I'm staying.

558
00:39:12,079 --> 00:39:14,440
Well, taking inspiration
from your answer...

559
00:39:16,519 --> 00:39:19,079
I'd say it leaves us
in a very similar place.

560
00:39:20,599 --> 00:39:21,519
You're here...

561
00:39:22,079 --> 00:39:22,960
And I'm here.

562
00:39:25,119 --> 00:39:29,199
After all the bad stuff that's happened,
that's a good thing, right?

563
00:39:29,559 --> 00:39:30,440
I'd say so.

564
00:39:31,559 --> 00:39:33,960
Hey, sorry, have you seen Ander?

565
00:39:34,039 --> 00:39:36,199
No, but don't stop looking.

566
00:39:38,039 --> 00:39:40,280
Everyone's looking for someone tonight.

567
00:39:40,760 --> 00:39:43,599
Luckily, some of us have found
what we were looking for.

568
00:40:03,679 --> 00:40:04,559
Hey, babe.

569
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:07,119
Hey.

570
00:40:17,519 --> 00:40:18,679
I didn't graduate.

571
00:40:21,960 --> 00:40:22,800
Me neither.

572
00:40:25,519 --> 00:40:27,719
Well... misery loves company.

573
00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:39,000
What will you do?

574
00:40:40,639 --> 00:40:43,239
-Repeat the school year or get a job?
-No.

575
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:48,840
I got an opportunity to go to New York.

576
00:40:50,119 --> 00:40:50,960
Really?

577
00:40:51,960 --> 00:40:52,800
Yeah.

578
00:40:54,480 --> 00:40:56,000
But not with your sister, right?

579
00:40:56,960 --> 00:40:58,440
No. I mean, yeah,

580
00:40:58,519 --> 00:41:01,760
at first, it was with her,
but after what happened...

581
00:41:02,599 --> 00:41:03,599
well...

582
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:05,920
I'm going with Malick.

583
00:41:14,920 --> 00:41:16,760
So, he'll help you get settled?

584
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:22,360
It all sounds too weird.

585
00:41:26,639 --> 00:41:28,000
Or too perfect.

586
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:30,960
Yeah, that too.

587
00:41:35,559 --> 00:41:36,639
What do you think?

588
00:41:37,199 --> 00:41:38,039
Me?

589
00:41:42,599 --> 00:41:43,760
Whatever you think.

590
00:41:47,079 --> 00:41:48,840
I think I need your opinion.

591
00:41:54,199 --> 00:41:57,159
Only an idiot would let something
that perfect slip away.

592
00:42:02,039 --> 00:42:02,880
Right.

593
00:42:05,440 --> 00:42:06,280
OK.

594
00:42:09,920 --> 00:42:11,360
-Omar.
-What?

595
00:42:16,639 --> 00:42:17,480
Goodbye.

596
00:43:00,119 --> 00:43:00,960
Hey, sexy.

597
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:02,960
Not now, Carla.

598
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:06,599
Why not now?
You don't even know what I'm gonna say.

599
00:43:13,639 --> 00:43:14,480
Look...

600
00:43:15,159 --> 00:43:18,400
it may surprise you to hear this,
but I was thinking--

601
00:43:24,880 --> 00:43:26,440
What the hell is he doing here?

602
